<dl id="n06051j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06051j">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06051j"> 51(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> in clowns</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A Marseille, dit le docteur Despine, lorsque le cirque du champ de foire est d&eacute;moli, on voit les gamins qui ont assist&eacute; aux exercices <mark>des clowns</mark>, s&apos;essayer, sur la place m&ecirc;me marqu&eacute;e par l&apos;ar&egrave;ne, &agrave; reproduire les tours de force dont ils ont &eacute;t&eacute; t&eacute;moins. <font color="green">[In Marseilles, says Dr. Despine, when the circus of the fairground is demolished, we see the kids who attended the exercises of the clowns, trying, in the square even marked by the arena, to reproduce the tour de force which they witnessed.]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 86</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
